headline: Up for 5th Senate Term, Collins Walks Impeachment Tightrope
abstract: The four-term Maine senator, who crossed party lines to vote against President Clinton’s impeachment, must now decide whether to break with President Trump.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A few days after Senator Susan Collins cast her votes to acquit President Bill Clinton, as she was greeted with icy stares at a Lincoln Day dinner in rural Maine, a fellow Republican approached her, irate.
keywords: Trump-Ukraine Whistle-blower Complaint and Impeachment Inquiry
